<a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>City of Joburg Emergency Management Services spokesman Robert Mulaudzi said 11 more shacks caught fire.“There were no other injuries reported. We want to urge residents to exercise caution when lighting candles or using paraffin stoves. This will help avoid devastating incidents like this one,” said Mulaudzi. He said the area doesn’t have power, which tends to lead to many fire incidents.Mulaudszi urged residents, especially in squatter camps, not to leave candles and paraffin stoves unattended.These were safety tips given by emergency services:Parents should teach their children that fire is dangerous and not to play with matchesBe careful when using a primus stove and never leave it unattendedWhen using gas appliances, make sure there are no gas leaks in the connection and that the gas cylinder is in a good condition, and in a well ventilated area.No one should smoke in bed.Candles are a big fire hazard. When children use candles, it should be under parental or adult supervision.Candles also need to be put in proper holders to prevent them from falling over and starting a fire.